docs.lead_paragraph: The city of Louisville, Ky., has agreed to pay $2 million to settle lawsuits brought by the boyfriend of Breonna Taylor, a Black woman who was fatally shot by police officers in 2020 and whose death ignited nationwide protests against police brutality, according to one of his lawyers.

headline.main: Louisville to Pay $2 Million to Breonna Taylor’s Boyfriend, Lawyer Says

docs.abstract: The son of Coventry factory workers, he overcame a traumatic childhood to find fame in the Thatcher years as the frontman of the Specials.

docs.lead_paragraph: Terry Hall, the frontman of the Specials, the British ska band that blended pub-fight energy with socially conscious lyrics that explored the political and racial tensions of Britain in the late 1970s and early ’80s, died on Dec. 18. He was 63.

headline.main: Terry Hall, a Face of Britain’s Ska Revival, Is Dead at 63
headline.print_headline: Terry Hall, 63; His Weary Rage Stoked a Ska Revival

docs.abstract: When does a nation of heretics leave its Christian origins behind?
docs.snippet: When does a nation of heretics leave its Christian origins behind?
docs.lead_paragraph: In September the Pew Research Center modeled four potential futures for American religion, depending on different rates of conversion to and disaffiliation from the nation’s faiths. In three of the four projections, the Christian percentage of the U.S. population, which hovered around 90 percent in the 1970s and 1980s, drops below 50 percent within the next half-century. In two scenarios, the Christian share drops below 50 percent much sooner, sometime around 2040, and then keeps on falling.

keywords.name: creative_works
keywords.value: Bad Religion: How We Became a Nation of Heretics (Book)

docs.abstract: A report organized by the league and its players union added yet more stinging information about how the league was mismanaged and how it mistreated its players. It described instances of sexual abuse, unwanted sexual advances by a general manager, emotional abuse, cronyism, racist remarks, the blurring of professional boundaries and retaliation of players who complained about their mistreatment.
